name: Drawing Circles is Fun
description:
There are a set of points S on the plane. This set doesn't contain the origin
O(0, 0), and for each two distinct points in the set A and B, the triangle OAB
has strictly positive area. Consider a set of pairs of points (P1, P2), (P3,
P4), ..., (P2k - 1, P2k). We'll call the set good if and only if: k ≥ 2. All
Pi are distinct, and each Pi is an element of S. For any two pairs (P2i - 1,
P2i) and (P2j - 1, P2j), the circumcircles of triangles OP2i - 1P2j - 1 and
OP2iP2j have a single common point, and the circumcircle of triangles OP2i -
1P2j and OP2iP2j - 1 have a single common point. Calculate the number of good
sets of pairs modulo 1000000007 (10^9 + 7). Input The first line contains a
single integer n (1 ≤ n ≤ 1000) — the number of points in S. Each of the next
n lines contains four integers ai, bi, ci, di (0 ≤ |ai|, |ci| ≤ 50; 1 ≤ bi, di
≤ 50; (ai, ci) ≠ (0, 0)). These integers represent a point . No two points
coincide. Output Print a single integer — the answer to the problem modulo
1000000007 (10^9 + 7). Examples Input 10 -46 46 0 36 0 20 -24 48 -50 50 -49 49
-20 50 8 40 -15 30 14 28 4 10 -4 5 6 15 8 10 -20 50 -3 15 4 34 -16 34 16 34 2
17 Output 2 Input 10 30 30 -26 26 0 15 -36 36 -28 28 -34 34 10 10 0 4 -8 20 40
50 9 45 12 30 6 15 7 35 36 45 -8 20 -16 34 -4 34 4 34 8 17 Output 4 Input 10 0
20 38 38 -30 30 -13 13 -11 11 16 16 30 30 0 37 6 30 -4 10 6 15 12 15 -4 5 -10
25 -16 20 4 10 8 17 -2 17 16 34 2 17 Output 10
